column1: Never tell anyone the real reason you did something unless it is useful to do so.
column2: The best way to handle people is to tell them what they want to hear.
column3: One should take action only when sure it is morally right.
column4: Most people are basically good and kind.
column5: It is safest to assume that all people have a vicious streak and it will come out when they are given a chance.
column6: Honesty is the best policy in all cases.
column7: There is no excuse for lying to someone else.
column8: Generally speaking people wont work hard unless theyre forced to do so.
column9: All in all it is better to be humble and honest than to be important and dishonest.
column10: When you ask someone to do something for you it is best to give the real reasons for wanting it rather than giving reasons which carry more weight.
column11: Most people who get ahead in the world lead clean moral lives.
column12: Anyone who completely trusts anyone else is asking for trouble.
column13: The biggest difference between most criminals and other people is that the criminals are stupid enough to get caught.
column15: It is wise to flatter important people.
column16: It is possible to be good in all respects.
column17: PT Barnum was wrong when he said that theres a sucker born every minute.
column18: It is hard to get ahead without cutting corners here and there.
column19: People suffering from incurable diseases should have the choice of being put painlessly to death.
column20: Most people forget more easily the death of their parents than the loss of their property.
